Unlike any Jack Daniels. Sweet with a layer of smoky oak finished with a smooth chocolate molasses flavor

Beautiful butterscotch hue, tingly sensations start to finish, smoother than you’d think, some sugar, Madagascar vanilla. 
Bittersweetness of intense dark chocolate, dripping off Granny Smith apples, pinch of sea salt (maybe two).

Interesting- jack Daniels elements with a little Marciano cherry and incredible smoothness - having side by side with weller 12 in the old bottle on my 40th birthday. Pretty good - but not worth 170. Cheers!
Was surprised this was a jd product.  Very good, complex, velvety.  Vanilla and spice
Smoothest whiskey I've ever had outside of Kentucky.  Possibly inclusive of Kentucky. I can't believe this is Jack Daniels.
Smooth on the nose and palate. Creamy, nutty, spicy, and honey on the tongue. Smooth.
